This paper discusses the use of Mobile Edge Computing (MEC) for next-generation wireless networks, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a distributed mechanism for computation offloading, which involves the activation of servers, which could fall under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of the theory of Minority Games, which could fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the satisfaction of users' quality-of-experience (QoE) requirements, which could fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
